<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="44">Discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="44">
Within the family Chiasmodontidae, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:55535F07-62E9-4F6D-B657-E2A1C6E9463F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus Lütken 1892:285" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudoscopelus</taxonomicName>
is the only genus with photophores, but two described species, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0A87D071-7FCE-4735-A63E-28D84313C501" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus aphos Prokofiev &amp; Kukuev 2005" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aphos">P. aphos</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parini">P. parini</taxonomicName>
, lack this characteristic. Prokofiev and Kukuev (2006c) provided other generic characteristics to define the genus, “characteristics of jaw dentition, (...) peculiarly striated and cancellated cranial roofing bones.” Teeth of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:55535F07-62E9-4F6D-B657-E2A1C6E9463F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus Lütken 1892:285" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudoscopelus</taxonomicName>
are of type 1 or 4, arranged in three series in the premaxilla, and two in the dentary (as described herein for 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lavenbergi">P. lavenbergi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bothrorrhinos">P. bothrorrhinos</taxonomicName>
), a pattern that is similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CBDF8830-9BA7-4116-81E6-11C317AFC452" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Dysalotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Dysalotus MacGilchrist 1905:268" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dysalotus</taxonomicName>
with specific variations. Similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:55535F07-62E9-4F6D-B657-E2A1C6E9463F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus Lütken 1892:285" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudoscopelus</taxonomicName>
, bones that form the roof of the cranium in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B9543C54-6827-40B2-8D80-EED6C11FB344" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Chiasmodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Chiasmodon Johnson 1864:408" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Chiasmodon</taxonomicName>
(i.e., supraoccipital, parietals, and frontals) are also grooved, with crests in the frontals.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="44">
The validity of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:55535F07-62E9-4F6D-B657-E2A1C6E9463F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus Lütken 1892:285" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudoscopelus</taxonomicName>
is supported by two synapomorphies present in all species: the dorsal margin of the orbit is formed by infraorbital 6; the position of the last infraorbital pore in the dorsal edge of the orbit is anterior to the middle of the pupil (see Fig. 2). It is further differentiated from 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:10B4DB64-6B5C-448A-9FF0-523395D70A67" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Kali" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Kali Lloyd 1909:154" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Kali</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CBDF8830-9BA7-4116-81E6-11C317AFC452" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Dysalotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Dysalotus MacGilchrist 1905:268" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dysalotus</taxonomicName>
by having a well calcified spoon-shaped nasal, in the lateral or anterior sides of the snout, covered by thin transparent skin (vs. nasal weakly calcified, circular but not spoon-shaped, positioned in the dorsal part of the snout, and covered by pigmented skin), and by having the last scale of the lateral line well separated from the penultimate scale and positioned over the lower lobe of the caudal fin (vs. last lateral-line scale contiguous with penultimate scale), and by the presence of pre- and postzygapophyses (vs. absent in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:10B4DB64-6B5C-448A-9FF0-523395D70A67" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Kali" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Kali Lloyd 1909:154" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Kali</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CBDF8830-9BA7-4116-81E6-11C317AFC452" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Dysalotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Dysalotus MacGilchrist 1905:268" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dysalotus</taxonomicName>
). From 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B9543C54-6827-40B2-8D80-EED6C11FB344" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Chiasmodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Chiasmodon Johnson 1864:408" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Chiasmodon</taxonomicName>
, it also differs by the absence of a well developed fang in the anterior edge of premaxilla (vs. fang present in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B9543C54-6827-40B2-8D80-EED6C11FB344" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Chiasmodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Chiasmodon Johnson 1864:408" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Chiasmodon</taxonomicName>
), and by a reduced number of pores associated with infraorbital 1 (4-5 vs. 8- 9 in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B9543C54-6827-40B2-8D80-EED6C11FB344" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Chiasmodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Chiasmodon Johnson 1864:408" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Chiasmodon</taxonomicName>
). As defined herein, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:86B3784A-A207-483D-8652-DB48465F86B3" authority="Fowler, 1934" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1934" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Myersiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Myersiscus Fowler 1934:361" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myersiscus</taxonomicName>
is regarded a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:55535F07-62E9-4F6D-B657-E2A1C6E9463F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus Lütken 1892:285" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudoscopelus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4E52642C-7884-4FD2-A8FA-B80C3894695C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus altipinnis Parr 1933:41" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="altipinnis">Pseudoscopelus altipinnis</taxonomicName>
was described by Parr (1933) based on two specimens collected off Cat Island, Bahamas. One year later, Fowler (1934) described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3D1C639E-A031-433F-941A-51FAB8A3C0A7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus microps Fowler 1934:359" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microps">P. microps</taxonomicName>
based on a single specimen collected in the Gulf of Boni, off Sulawesi Island, Indonesia, apparently not knowing about Parr’s work, nor describing 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3D1C639E-A031-433F-941A-51FAB8A3C0A7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus microps Fowler 1934:359" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microps">P. microps</taxonomicName>
adequately. Prokofiev and Kukuev (2005, 2006a) recognized eight species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:55535F07-62E9-4F6D-B657-E2A1C6E9463F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus Lütken 1892:285" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudoscopelus</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4E52642C-7884-4FD2-A8FA-B80C3894695C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus altipinnis Parr 1933:41" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="altipinnis">P. altipinnis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3D1C639E-A031-433F-941A-51FAB8A3C0A7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus microps Fowler 1934:359" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microps">P. microps</taxonomicName>
, as valid, even though they did not compare the type specimens of any species. Later, Prokofiev and Kukuev (2006c) followed Lavenberg (1974) in recognizing 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4E52642C-7884-4FD2-A8FA-B80C3894695C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus altipinnis Parr 1933:41" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="altipinnis">P. altipinnis</taxonomicName>
as the senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3D1C639E-A031-433F-941A-51FAB8A3C0A7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus microps Fowler 1934:359" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microps">P. microps</taxonomicName>
, and altered the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4E52642C-7884-4FD2-A8FA-B80C3894695C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus altipinnis Parr 1933:41" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="altipinnis">P. altipinnis</taxonomicName>
provided in their first work, although again they did not examine type specimens. A comparison of primary types by the senior author (MM) confirmed the status of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4E52642C-7884-4FD2-A8FA-B80C3894695C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus altipinnis Parr 1933:41" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="altipinnis">P. altipinnis</taxonomicName>
as the senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3D1C639E-A031-433F-941A-51FAB8A3C0A7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus microps Fowler 1934:359" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microps">P. microps</taxonomicName>
, in agreement with Lavenberg (1974).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="45">
Prokofiev and Kukuev (2006c) also followed Lavenberg (1974) in recognizing 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A65C3A37-795F-466F-B777-9485AA1B7F05" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus stellatus Beebe 1932:75" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stellatus">P. stellatus Beebe</taxonomicName>
(1932). 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A65C3A37-795F-466F-B777-9485AA1B7F05" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus stellatus Beebe 1932:75" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stellatus">Pseudoscopelus stellatus</taxonomicName>
was described based on five larval specimens between 6.5 mm and 20.3 mm, obtained off Bermuda. Beebe (1932:75) listed the lot NYZS 21155 as the type (now USNM 170941), and mentioned three other lots during the species description, considered as paratypes by Eschmeyer (2006): NYZS 21321, 1 (now CAS-SU 66494), 21404, 2 (now CAS-SU 66497), and 21456, 1 (CAS-SU 66496). The lot USNM 170941 clearly has photophores along the body, as described and illustrated by Beebe (1932:76), but the other lots lack photophores. A study of the ontogenetic changes in the photophore pattern of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:55535F07-62E9-4F6D-B657-E2A1C6E9463F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus Lütken 1892:285" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudoscopelus</taxonomicName>
is ongoing; meanwhile, the status of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A65C3A37-795F-466F-B777-9485AA1B7F05" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoscopelus stellatus Beebe 1932:75" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stellatus">P. stellatus</taxonomicName>
should be regarded as species inquerida.
</paragraph>
